A research group from Zhejiang University working on Knowledge Graph and Language Technologies

 
About Us       Projects

Research

The team is devoted to foundational innovations in the fields of Knowledge Graphs, Large Language Models and a variety of their applications.

Knowledge Graphs

Knowledge Graphs (KGs) model world knowledge in graph-like forms to facilitate search, query answering, recommendation, or analytics. Areas of our research include: automatic KG construction, neural reasoning with KG, KG augmented deep models, etc.

Large Language Models

Large Language Model (LLMs) are deep models pre-trained on large-scale corpus with general purposes. Areas of our research include: knowledge-aware prompts, model editing, language models reasoning, low-resource model training, etc.

AI in Network Science

Network is powerful in modeling complex phenomena in many domains such as biomedicine, sociology, or cognitive science. We develop novel AI approaches that cater specifically to data describing complex networks and systems.

Featured Projects

Milestones

Some recent milestones about the team. Read More...

  • 2023.6

    Our LLM framework KnowLM was released

    KnowLM is an open-source large-scale knowledgable language model framework

  • 2023.01

    Our new Nature Machine Intelligence article was accepted

    A new article "Knowledge graph-enhanced molecular contrastive learning with functional prompt. " was just release in official website of Nature Machine Intelligence.

  • 2022.01

    OpenBG was released jointly by Zhejiang University and Alibaba

    Zhejiang University and Aliaba group joint released OpenBG, an open business knowledge graph for sake of supporting open knoweldge graph research.

  • 2021.11

    Best paper awards from both CCKS2021 and IJCKG2021.

    The team won the best paper awards from both China Conference on Knowledge Graph and Semantic Computing (CCKS2021) and International Joint Conference on Knowledge Graph(IJCKG2021)
